article.description: Valjarevic's buzzer beater lifts Maine over Wagner
article.headline: Valjarevic's buzzer beater lifts Maine over Wagner
article.linkText: Valjarevic's buzzer beater lifts Maine over Wagner
article.story: BANGOR, Maine -- Zarko Valjarevic scored 17 points, including a buzzer-beating jumper in overtime, to lift Maine over Wagner 82-81 at the Cross Insurance Center on Tuesday night. Till Gloger tied a career-high with 21 points, Shawn Lawton added 18 and Aaron Calixte had 10 points and nine assists for Maine (1-5). Marcus Burton hit three free throws with 1:06 left in overtime, giving Wagner an 81-78 lead. Gloger grabbed an offensive rebound of a missed 3 by Valjarevic and Calixte made a layup to pull the Black Bears within one with 33 seconds left. Valjarevic fouled and Greg Senat missed the front end of a one-and-one 14 seconds later. Valjarevic missed a jumper with 4 seconds to go, but the ball went out of bounds off of Wagner (2-4), setting up the winner as time expired. Burton scored a career-high 25 to lead Wagner. Mike Aaman added 15 points and 11 rebounds.
